First thing is, I want to see my Great-Grandmother !  We didn't manage to spend her 90th birthday together because of this circuit breaker. She's considered vulnerable because of ageand her immune system is not that strong so we only did a FaceTime call with the family and celebrated with herbut she hated it and swears that one looks way worse on a video call ❤ And also have a good catch-up hangout sesh with my friends . We've been Zoom-ing and Finding ways to play online game to spent time with one another and Spending time together ! Hope to see my friends and go out together again and my great-grandmother and family members when circuit breaker ends ! See you all soon ❤❤ @ghuiiyiing @baby_mlow @lepetite.mama

Hope to WIN WIN WIN this $50 Capitaland voucher from @toshibaacsg for my dearest mummy to thank her for being such a SUPERMOM through all these years of upbringing 🤗🤗
To the Queen of my Heart:
1) Provider 
You have been a steady provider and works to see that our family has the necessities of life. You have been a loyal employee in your job for the past 35 years. Given at the age of 6️⃣0️⃣, you seldom complain about being lethargic even when you need to take care of your grandchildren  during your post-retirement stage.
2) Teacher
You always willingly share your knowledge and principles to help us grow and develop over the years. You never allow us to take things for granted and always remind us to cherish what we have at the present. From the food on the table to the good education you have paid for, you will make us appreciate the values in everything we have!
3) Friend
You naturally show kindness, compassion and interest in our family. Whenever you are 🆓, you will spare some time to listen to us and have a good chat with us. You are just like everyone's best friend in the family! 
4) Exemplar
You show by the way you live an example of what the family stands for. You will not smoke if you don't want us to do it, and likewise does not drink heavily if you do not want us to do so. You taught us to deal with conflict in our family and with others by being firm but reasonable at the same time! 
5) Patriarch
You are honoured because of your moral character and actions. You don't expect us to live the same kind of life you do, and do the same kind of work. You respected our values and opinions, as long as they don't harm the family or anyone else! 
6) Disciplinarian
You helped us learn proper boundaries and consequences. You will strongly disapprove any of our misdeeds by using tough love to prove a point. You did this through the power of your words, not your fists. Likewise, you don't reward us for actions that are expected of us, such as helping with house chores or performing well in school!
@potatoeeeez_ @kwok.james @kimchoo3839

👩‍👧I miss my mum so much! I am so thankful & grateful that we are ending the circuit breaker very soon and some of the measures will be lifted so that I am finally allowed to visit my mum 👩‍👧and have a good hearty & heartwarming meal with her. I didn’t get to spend and celebrate Mother’s Day with her this year. I wish I had hugged her tighter and hold her hand longer the last time I met her.  I am so looking forward to meeting her next month to have home-cooked meal and forge more precious family moments feasting together. 😋 Nothing delight our hearts & satisfy our souls than comfort food cooked from the heart! ❤️ Looking forward to spending and enjoying quality family time bonding with my mum ! Can’t wait to indulge in a delectable spread with my mum to have a truly unforgettable family meal! 💗 @casperboi.171119 @hannchih.2589 @stephaniewong35
